post_text:
In an effort to prevent the spread of the COVID-19 virus within our staff and student body we are asking all parents/guardians, of students who will be in attendance on-site, and all employees to notify our designated Point of Contact immediately when the following occurs:

‚Ä¢Someone in the household has tested positive for COVID-19.
‚Ä¢Someone in the household has been identified as a Close Contact to a positive case of COVID-19 and is requiring quarantine and/or recommended to be tested for COVID-19.
‚Ä¢Student attending on-site and employees who are being tested for COVID-19. If symptomatic, student/staff should remain in quarantine pending results of their COVID-19 test.

Please call or text Meghan Wolfinbarger at 479-244-0004, or email information to mwolfinbarger@es.k12.ar.us. Thank you in advance for your cooperation. Together we can help keep our Eureka Springs School District family safe, healthy and ready to learn during this unique time.

Mrs. Holt, Ms. Lisa & the Middle school staff are ready for you to come back!!

A few reminders:

On-Site students grades 5th & 7th will begin Monday, August 24th. On-Site students 6th & 8th grade will begin on Tuesday, August 25th. All On-Site students will come to school on Wednesday, August 26th. This soft opening will allow students, teachers & staff to safely practice the new protocols required by the state due to Covid-19.

Students should arrive between 7:30 - 7:45 am. The first bell will ring at 7:50
am. School will dismiss at 3:01 pm.

We hope everyone has viewed the welcome videos Mrs. Holt & our amazing teachers have posted on our Middle School webpage & Facebook! We are ready to see everyone & prepared for a good year!

MIDDLE SCHOOL PARENTS & STUDENTS:

Middle School Start Days:

On-Site students in grades 5th and 7th will attend on August 24th. On-Site students in grades 6th and 8th will attend on August 25th.

This staggered opening will allow teachers/students to practice and establish safety protocols that will be required due to the Covid-10 pandemic. ALL on-site students will attend Wednesday,August 26th, moving forward.

**Class schedules for students in 7th and 8th grade will be mailed out before school begins. Please bring your schedule on the first day of school to avoid delays.

For On-site students: Chromebooks and supplies will be available during our first week in classes. These will NOT be distributed before school opens.

**REMINDER: If you have not registered your students, please do so at this time. We are preparing classrooms, schedules and admittance for the 2020-2021 school year.

Attention HIGH SCHOOL PARENTS AND STUDENTS considering the virtual option this year:
A prerecorded video will be posted this Friday on our school Facebook page to discuss procedures and expectations for the VIRTUAL option. We will be covering what the virtual option looks like for all high school students as well as procedures, expectations, and technology requirements to be an effective virtual student. We would like to address any questions parents may have. Please submit questions in this post that you may have before Friday morning and we will address those in the video. You can also contact the high school office at 479-253-8875 or email Principal David Gilmore david.gilmore@es.k12.ar.us

post_text:
It‚Äôs FINALLY Graduation time!!!! üë®üèº‚Äçüéì

-Saturday, July 11th- 10am
-Eureka Springs Track
-All students received tickets at practice on Friday.
-Seniors must be in the middle school gym by 9:30am.
-All attendees must wear a mask and enter with a ticket.
-Bring your own chair. We suggest water as well.
-You will be directed to parking as you enter our campus.
-No umbrellas or anything to obstruct the view for others.
-Graduation will be live on our FaceBook page.

****In the event of a pop-up storm, we will move graduation to Saturday at 1pm. In the event of all day storms, we will move graduation to Sunday at 1pm. Any changes will be posted and robocall will be made.****

Melanie Myhre Photography will be available directly after graduation in the middle school gym for senior photos. Packages may be purchased.

Congrats to the Class of 2020!!

SUMMER MEALS for SCHOOL KIDS

The 1st delivery for Phase 2 of Answering The Call is in the books.

The 2nd delivery will be next Monday, July 13 and will continue every Monday through August 10.

Meal bags are available to any kid 18 or under in Western Carroll County, regardless of school attended, including homeschool. Eureka Springs Schools, Academy of Excellence, Clear Spring School...any school.

Delivered directly to your doorstep, totally FREE.

To register for meals for your child, just call Martie at 479-253-8987, or email her at esfumc@sbcglobal.net.

To volunteer to help deliver, please message Bill on Facebook or email bill@atcforeureka.com.

Please share.

#NoKidGoesHungry
#JustCallMartie

post_text:
Eureka Springs Elementary School would like to welcome Ms. Molly Murray to the team!

"Hello! My name is Molly Murray. I am excited to be joining the First Grade team. I completed my Bachelor of Arts in Interdisciplinary Studies through Western Governors University and am certified to teach Kindergarten-Eighth Grade.
I grew up in Southwest Colorado and moved to Northwest Arkansas in 2007. My husband and I live in Eureka Springs with our two children. We enjoy exploring the great outdoors and spending time with family.
While completing my degree, I worked as a church office manager in Fayetteville, AR. Prior to my time as an office manager, I spent seven years working with children and teens struggling with mental and behavioral health challenges. I was a substitute teacher during the 2019-20 school year at Eureka Springs Schools. I look forward to being a part of the wonderful team at Eureka Springs Elementary School!"

The meal deliveries from the Eureka Springs School District will end on June 30th. We thank all of the volunteers for their diligent work and organization for the past several months!!!

If you are a family that would still need meal services, we invite you to contact Answering The Call. The Eureka Springs Methodist Church and their volunteers have been wonderful in assuring that all needs are met and we thank them for contacting the school and offering to continue this service for our families. While we are in the summer months, please register for meal delivery by calling Martie at 479-253-8987 or emailing esfumc@sbcglobal.net

To volunteer to help deliver meals, message Bill Featherstone on Facebook or email bill@atcforeureka.com

To donate and provide more meals for more people, go to atcforeureka.com or message Bill for instructions on where to mail or drop off a check.

Happy Friday, Middle School Students and Parents!! Here is an announcement from Mrs. Holt:

Middle School packets will be due Friday, April 17th. This will be for any AMI work for the weeks of March 17- April 3rd. And the recent AMI packets dated April 6th - April 17th. NEW packets for the week of April 20th-May 1st, will be ready for pick up, outside the middle school, on Monday, April 20th.

All the staff at the middle school, are working hard to help you succeed in your academics during this interesting situation. We hope you are staying safe, washing your hands and enjoying your families.

post_text:
Hey there families and students! A couple things to mention:

1. Per Governor Hutchinson, public schools will remain closed for the rest of the school year. We will continue with AMIs and virtual learning depending on your school building. Please stay in close contact with your child's teacher(s) as they will continue to give you guidance throughout this process.

2. This week, busses will NOT run food routes on Thursday. They will deliver double on Wednesday so everyone has enough food. AMI collection will continue at bus stops if anyone wants to drop anything.

3. Starting on Monday, April 13th to limit exposure, busses will run on Monday, Wednesday, Friday ONLY. They will double up on food to deliver to our families. That schedule will be in effect for the remainer of our delivery services.

Stay well! We miss everyone's smiling faces!!

post_text:
Families,
Meal delivery will begin on Monday, March 30th. Each day, bus routes will run and drivers will deliver breakfast and lunch food to students in need. Busses will leave the school daily just after 11am to begin bus routes. If you have signed up, plan to meet at the closest bus stop, the driver will be aware and there will be a teacher on board to meet you. If you do not know where the closest stop is, contact the bus shop during school hours 253-5982.

This applies to ALL students, not just bus riders. Daily delivery will continue Monday-Friday until we return to school. Teachers will also collect any AMI work that needs to be returned to the school. Please be flexible as we run the busses the first few days. We apologize for not having exact times.

You can still sign up by clicking the 'SEND EMAIL' button at the top of the FaceBook page and submitting the following:
-Parent Name
-Student Name(s)
-Number of meals needed daily
-Address
-Contact Number

You will remain on the daily roster until you notify us that you would like to be removed. Thank you!!

2. Circles and Friends

4. Relationships and Love

post_text: Levi Crider, Ethan Weems, and Baxter Hager finished in 2nd place (Gold Tier) in the state of Arkansas in this year's CyberPatriot competition. They came in on four separate weekends to spend six hours each time competing against the other teams in Arkansas. They use the time in their EAST class to prepare for the competition. CyberPatriot is the National Youth Cyber Education Program created by the Air Force Association to inspire K-12 students toward careers in cybersecurity or other science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) disciplines critical to our nation's future.

Senior Hunter Chapman had a great idea for his EAST project to bring in speakers and talk to students about mental health awareness. For the last three days, teens had the option to attend the following sessions during their 20 minute advisory block:

-How to Tell If a Friend Needs Help
-Stress and Anxiety
-Mindfulness

Students left with great comments and are even asking about future sessions. Thanks to Steve, Nicole and Tina for sharing their knowledge with us! ‚ù§Ô∏è

shared_text:
Mrs. Hyatt - High School Counselor
November 25, 2019 at 8:51 PM ¬∑

We now offer a Grief Group for students who have lost a parent. This is generously funded by the Ratzlaff Legacy Foundation in hopes that students can relate to one another while experiencing fun activities together.

The family of Senior Chief Petty Officer (SEAL) Thomas A. Ratzlaff funds this program from proceeds of The Rat Race which is held in Green Forest each year. This event remembers the 31 heroes lost on 8-6-2011 during Extortion 17.

While thinking of his children and their loss, they wanted to assist other children in schools. If you are a parent or family member with a child in our schools who could benefit from this program, PLEASE contact me: rhyatt@es.k12.ar.us

I lost my father at 11 and know that being around other students that knew what I was feeling could have made a huge difference. On a personal note, I so much appreciate the assistance of the Ratzlaff family to our students and the sacrifice of Senior Chief Petty Officer Thomas A. Ratzlaff to our country. üá∫üá∏‚ù§Ô∏è

post_text: A chunk of our PreK-12 staff spent their day in Mental Health First Aid Training with the Arkansas AWARE team today! This is round two of this training in our district. We are proud to say that we are attempting to train ALL staff in this area (teachers, librarians, counselors, custodians, special ed staff, etc) so that every member of our team can recognize and assist our students with their mental health needs. We are thankful for the Arkansas AWARE team in our district and their impact on us and our students! ‚ù§Ô∏è
